text: Eupraxia may refer to: * Eupraxia (mythology) * Eupraxia - the art of performing a function correctly as discussed in the Memorabilia (Xenophon) * Eupraxia or Euphrasia of Constantinople * Eupraxia of Kiev, Holy Roman Empress. ==See also== * Praxis (disambiguation) * Dyspraxia
title: Eupraxia
